\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 After the final bell rang, signaling the end of the school day, Haruki and Honoka walked together through the hallway, their footsteps blending with the chatter of other students. The air was filled with the sound of laughter and the shuffling of shoes as everyone made their way to the exits.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki glanced at Honoka, her hands clutching the straps of her bag. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Aoki-san,\u8221\'94 she began, her tone hesitant, \u8220\'93I-is the class usually this strict?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka looked at her, her brow furrowing in confusion. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Strict? I thought it was pretty laid back today. Why? Was it different at your previous school?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki hesitated, unsure of how much to reveal. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Well\u8230\'85 yeah,\u8221\'94 she said carefully. \u8220\'93At my old school, the teachers were usually pretty relaxed. Sometimes, we could even talk to them like friends. But here\u8230\'85\u8221\'94 She trailed off, glancing around the hallway as if expecting Mr. Genzo to appear with his wooden ruler at any moment. \u8220\'93It feels like I could get hit with a ruler for just breathing wrong.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka giggled, covering her mouth with her hand. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You\u8217\'92re funny, Fujiyama-san. Are you from the city or something? I\u8217\'92ve heard the schools there are a lot more laid back.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki blinked, caught off guard by the question. She couldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t exactly tell Honoka that she was from the same town, just fifty years in the future. So, she nodded, going along with the assumption. \u8220\'93Yeah, I\u8217\'92m from the city. It\u8217\'92s\u8230\'85 different there.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s eyes sparkled with curiosity. \u8220\'93That sounds exciting. I\u8217\'92ve always wanted to visit the city. Maybe one day I will.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki smiled faintly, though her heart ached at the thought. She knew what the future held for Honoka\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 a life tied to tradition and expectations, far removed from the dreams she might have now.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka tilted her head, studying Haruki for a moment. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You know, if it helps you relax a bit, you can just call me Honoka.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s eyes widened in surprise. \u8220\'93A-are you sure?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka nodded, her smile warm and genuine. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Of course. We\u8217\'92re classmates now, after all.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki hesitated, then nodded. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Alright then, Honoka-san,\u8221\'94 she said, testing the name on her tongue. \u8220\'93Then please call me Haruki.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s smile widened. \u8220\'93Okay then, Haruki-chan.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The nickname caught Haruki off guard, sending a warm, familiar feeling through her chest. She hadn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t been called that in a long time. In the present, her mother always addressed her formally, her tone strict and distant. But here, Honoka\u8217\'92s voice was friendly and down-to-earth, filled with a warmth that felt both familiar and alien at the same time.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 It was strange, hearing her mother\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 her\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 young}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~mother\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 call her by such an affectionate name. It made her feel at home, yet also reminded her of how much had changed over the years. How much\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 she}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~had changed.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 As they walked through the bustling hallway, Honoka turned to Haruki with a bright smile. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93By the way, Haruki-chan,\u8221\'94 she said, her tone casual but enthusiastic, \u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m the editor of the Literature Club. If you haven\u8217\'92t joined any clubs yet, you should consider joining mine. We\u8217\'92re always looking for someone to help out with the papers!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki hesitated, her mind racing. The Literature Club. It wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t the Art Club she had loved so much in her own time, but it was something. Still, after everything that had happened today, she felt exhausted\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 mentally and emotionally. She needed time to process everything.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Thank you, Honoka-san,\u8221\'94 Haruki said, forcing a small smile. \u8220\'93I\u8217\'92ll think about it. But today\u8230\'85 I think I just need to rest. It\u8217\'92s been quite a day.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka nodded, her expression understanding. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Of course. You\u8217\'92ve had a lot to adjust to. Take your time.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 They continued walking, the chatter of other students fading as they neared the school gates. Honoka glanced at Haruki, her curiosity getting the better of her. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93So, where do you live, Haruki-chan? Maybe we\u8217\'92re neighbors!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s heart skipped a beat. She hadn\u8217\'92t thought about this. Her house\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 the grand, traditional estate she knew in the present\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 didn\u8217\'92t exist yet. The only place she could call home in this time was the small, abandoned house in the forest where she had taken shelter the night before. She needed to come up with something believable.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I, uh\u8230\'85 live in a cabin in the forest,\u8221\'94 Haruki said, her voice hesitant. \u8220\'93With my grandfather.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s eyes widened in surprise. \u8220\'93Really? That\u8217\'92s so interesting! I didn\u8217\'92t know there were cabins out there. I live not far from the forest, actually. My family\u8217\'92s house is just a short walk away.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s mind raced. That\u8217\'92s right\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 her grandparents\u8217\'92 house on her mother\u8217\'92s side was somewhere near the forest. She had heard stories about it from her mother, though she had never seen it herself. The realization made her chest tighten with a strange mix of emotions.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh,\u8221\'94 Haruki said, her voice soft. \u8220\'93That\u8217\'92s\u8230\'85 convenient.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka smiled, her expression warm. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93If you\u8217\'92re heading home now, we could walk together. It\u8217\'92s always nicer to have company, don\u8217\'92t you think?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki hesitated for a moment, then nodded. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Sure. That sounds nice.\u8221\'94}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 They stepped out of the school gates, the cool afternoon air brushing against their faces. The sun was beginning to set, casting a golden glow over the town. As they walked, Honoka chatted easily, telling Haruki about her family, her favorite books, and the Literature Club\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s upcoming activities. Haruki listened, her heart swelling with a mix of emotions\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 nostalgia, sadness, and a strange, aching hope.}
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 As they walked toward the gate, Haruki noticed a group of students gathered nearby. The motorcycle gang from earlier was hanging out, their bikes parked in a neat row. Nagano sat on the edge of the sidewalk, an acoustic guitar resting on his lap. His fingers moved skillfully over the strings, playing a familiar tune\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 }{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 Ue o Muite Aruk\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u333\'6F}{\f0\fs24\b0 \hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 while his friends sang along, their voices loud and slightly off-key.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Hey, it\u8217\'92s Haruki-chan!\u8221\'94 Nagano called, spotting her as she approached. He grinned, his fingers still strumming the guitar. \u8220\'93Come join us!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki smiled, her heart lifting at the sight. She turned to Honoka, who was standing beside her, her face suddenly flushed and her hands fidgeting nervously. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Hey, it\u8217\'92s Nagano over there,\u8221\'94 Haruki said, her tone cheerful. \u8220\'93Let\u8217\'92s go say hi!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93H-Haruki?\u8221\'94 Honoka stammered, her voice barely above a whisper. Her cheeks turned bright red, and she looked like she wanted to disappear. But before she could protest, Haruki grabbed her hand and pulled her toward the group.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Nagano\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s grin widened as they approached. \u8220\'93Hey, Haruki-chan! And\u8230\'85 oh, it\u8217\'92s Aoki-san!\u8221\'94 he said, his tone teasing. \u8220\'93What brings you two here?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s face turned even redder, and she looked down at her feet, unable to meet Nagano\u8217\'92s gaze. \u8220\'93I-I was just walking home with Fujiyama-san,\u8221\'94 she mumbled, her voice barely audible.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki, on the other hand, was unfazed. She let go of Honoka\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s hand and sat down on the sidewalk, leaning back on her palms. \u8220\'93We heard you playing and thought we\u8217\'92d come over,\u8221\'94 she said, her tone casual. \u8220\'93You\u8217\'92re pretty good, Nagano.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Nagano laughed, his fingers still moving over the guitar strings. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Thanks! I\u8217\'92ve been practicing. You know this song?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki nodded. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yeah, it\u8217\'92s\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 Ue o Muite Aruk\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u333\'6F}{\f0\fs24\b0 , right? It\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s a a vintage classic.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Nagano\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s fingers faltered for a moment, and he looked at her with a puzzled expression. \u8220\'93Vintage? What are you talking about? This song just came out last year. It\u8217\'92s a global hit right now\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 everyone even people in America is listening to it.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki froze, her cheeks flushing as she realized her mistake. Of course. She wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t in the present anymore. This song wasn\u8217\'92t a nostalgic throwback here\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 it was brand new, fresh and popular. And her parents\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 well, the younger versions of them sitting right here\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 were part of the generation that had made it a hit.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, right,\u8221\'94 Haruki said quickly, trying to cover her slip. \u8220\'93I mean, it\u8217\'92s just so good that it feels like a classic already.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I know, right?\u8221\'94, He grinned, and started playing again. \u8220\'93Well, if you like it that much, maybe I\u8217\'92ll play it more often.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki smiled weakly, her mind racing. She couldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t help but think about her father in the present, how he would play this song on his old tape recorder whenever he was relaxing by himself. She had always thought it was just a random habit, but now she realized\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 this was where it had started. This song, this moment, was the origin of that tradition.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka, still standing awkwardly to the side, finally found her voice. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I-It\u8217\'92s\u8230\'85 it\u8217\'92s a beautiful song,\u8221\'94 she said softly, her eyes flickering toward Nagano before quickly looking away.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Nagano smiled at her, his expression softening. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Thanks, Aoki-san. You should sit down and sing with us. We\u8217\'92re just hanging out before heading home.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka hesitated, her face still flushed, but Haruki reached up and tugged on her sleeve. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Come on, Honoka-san. Sit down. It\u8217\'92ll be fun.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Reluctantly, Honoka sat down beside Haruki, her hands folded neatly in her lap. Nagano continued playing, his friends joining in with the singing. The atmosphere was lively and carefree, a stark contrast to the strict, formal environment of the school.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 As the music filled the air, Haruki couldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t help but smile. For the first time since arriving in this strange, unfamiliar world, she felt a sense of belonging. She glanced at Honoka, who was still blushing but seemed to be enjoying herself, and then at Nagano, who was completely absorbed in his music.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 This was her parents\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92 past\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 a time before the weight of expectations and responsibilities had shaped them into the people she knew. And for now, she was a part of it.}
