\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 As Haruki and Honoka continued their walk home, the sun dipped lower in the sky, casting a warm, golden glow over the rice fields that stretched out on either side of the road. The air was filled with the chirping of crickets and the occasional rustle of the wind through the tall grass. It was peaceful, but Honoka\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s mood was anything but.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 She walked a few steps ahead of Haruki, her arms crossed and her lips pressed into a pout. Her shoulders were hunched, and every now and then, she let out a small, frustrated sigh. Haruki watched her with amusement, recognizing the sulky demeanor all too well. It was so much like her mother in the present\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 stubborn, dramatic, and impossible to ignore.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Honoka-san,\u8221\'94 Haruki said, her tone light and teasing. \u8220\'93What\u8217\'92s the matter? You\u8217\'92ve been sulking the whole way.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka mumbled something under her breath, her voice barely audible.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What was that?\u8221\'94 Haruki asked, leaning closer.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I said,\u8221\'94 Honoka repeated, her voice louder but still tinged with annoyance, \u8220\'93You should\u8217\'92ve given me a heads-up before dragging me over there like that.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki blinked, surprised by the response. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93A heads-up? About what?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka stopped walking and turned to face Haruki, her cheeks flushed and her eyes narrowed. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93About Nagano and his friends, obviously! You just pulled me over without warning, and I wasn\u8217\'92t ready!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki stared at her for a moment, then burst out laughing. The way Honoka sulked and grumbled, her mannerisms and tone\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 it was so reminiscent of her present-day mother. It took Haruki a second to realize what was happening, but when it clicked, she couldn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t stop grinning.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, I see,\u8221\'94 Haruki said, her voice dripping with mock seriousness. \u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s about Nagano-kun, isn\u8217\'92t it?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s face turned bright red, and she sputtered, \u8220\'93Wh-what? Where did that come from?!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki smirked, crossing her arms. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Come on, Honoka-san! It\u8217\'92s obvious!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Sh-shh!\u8221\'94 Honoka hissed, lunging forward and clapping a hand over Haruki\u8217\'92s mouth. She glanced around nervously, her eyes scanning the empty road and the vast rice fields around them. Satisfied that no one was nearby, she slowly removed her hand and let out a long sigh.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You\u8217\'92re impossible,\u8221\'94 Honoka muttered, her cheeks still flushed. She hesitated for a moment, then sighed again, her shoulders slumping. \u8220\'93Fine. I trust you, Haruki-chan. So\u8230\'85 I\u8217\'92ll tell you.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki raised an eyebrow, trying to suppress a smile. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Tell me what?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka looked down at her feet, her voice barely above a whisper. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8230\'85 I like Nagano-kun.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 There was a beat of silence. Haruki\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s expression didn\u8217\'92t change\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 it remained deadpan, almost unreadable\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 but a small, involuntary chuckle escaped her lips. The absurdity of the situation hit her all at once. Here she was, standing in the middle of a rice field in 1961, listening to her teenage mother confess her crush on her teenage father. It was like something out of a surreal comedy.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s eyes widened, and she stared at Haruki, her confusion evident. \u8220\'93W-what is that reaction?\u8221\'94 she asked, her voice rising in panic. \u8220\'93Is it that obvious?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s lips twitched again, but she managed to keep her expression mostly neutral. \u8220\'93Oh, no, no,\u8221\'94 she said, her tone dripping with mock seriousness. \u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s not obvious at all. I\u8217\'92m just\u8230\'85 processing.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka frowned, clearly not buying it. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Processing? What does that even mean?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki shrugged, her deadpan expression finally breaking into a small grin. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It means you\u8217\'92re not as subtle as you think, Honoka-san.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka groaned, covering her face with her hands. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93This is a disaster.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki reached out and gently pulled Honoka\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s hands away from her face. \u8220\'93Hey, it\u8217\'92s not a disaster. It\u8217\'92s cute. And honestly, I think Nagano-kun likes you too.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s expression shifted, her earlier flustered demeanor giving way to something more somber. She took her hands away from her face, her voice quiet but firm. \u8220\'93No, he doesn\u8217\'92t.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t you see how popular he is?}{\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 Honoka continued, \u8220\'93He\u8217\'92s surrounded by all those popular boys, and the girls in class\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 no, the entire school\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 are always talking about him. About how cool he is, about the rumors of him defying the principal, how he avoids punishments and not being scared by it.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki blinked, surprised by the sudden shift in Honoka\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s mood. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m just an editor for the school press in the Literature Club,\u8221\'94 Honoka continued, her voice trembling slightly. \u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m not popular. In fact, my name isn\u8217\'92t even written in the school press. No one notices me unless they need something proofread. You\u8217\'92re the only one who actually talks to me and doesn\u8217\'92t think my rambling about books and literature is boring.\u8221\'94 She looked down at her feet, her shoulders slumping. \u8220\'93What chance do I have with someone like Nagano-kun?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s heart ached at the raw vulnerability in Honoka\u8217\'92s voice. She had always known her mother as a strong, confident woman in the present, but here, in this time, Honoka was just a teenager, grappling with insecurities and self-doubt. It was a side of her mother she had never seen before, and it made her feel both protective and sad.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Honoka-san,\u8221\'94 Haruki said gently, placing a hand on her shoulder. \u8220\'93You\u8217\'92re amazing. You\u8217\'92re smart, kind, and passionate about what you love. That\u8217\'92s not something everyone has. And Nagano-kun\u8230\'85 he\u8217\'92s not as untouchable as you think. He\u8217\'92s just a guy who likes music, motorcycles and hanging out with his friends. Trust me, he\u8217\'92d be lucky to have someone like you.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka looked up at Haruki, her eyes glistening with unshed tears. For a moment, it seemed like she wanted to believe her, but then she shook her head again. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It doesn\u8217\'92t matter. Even if he did like me, it wouldn\u8217\'92t change anything. I\u8217\'92m not\u8230\'85 I\u8217\'92m not the kind of girl he would even notice.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki opened her mouth to argue, }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 But Honoka cut her off. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Please, Haruki-chan,\u8221\'94 she said, her voice pleading. \u8220\'93Just\u8230\'85 keep this a secret, okay? I don\u8217\'92t want it to turn into some rumor. I don\u8217\'92t want to be laughed at.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki hesitated, then nodded. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Okay,\u8221\'94 she said softly. \u8220\'93I won\u8217\'92t tell anyone. But just know that you\u8217\'92re worth more than you think, Honoka-san. And someday, someone\u8217\'92s going to see that. Maybe even Nagano-kun.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka gave her a small, grateful smile, though it didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t quite reach her eyes. \u8220\'93Thanks, Haruki-chan. You\u8217\'92re a good friend.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 They continued walking in silence, the weight of Honoka\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s confession hanging in the air. Haruki couldn\u8217\'92t help but feel a mix of emotions\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 sadness for Honoka\u8217\'92s insecurities, frustration at the unfairness of it all, and a fierce determination to help her mother see her own worth.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 For the first time since arriving in this strange, unfamiliar world, Haruki felt a flicker of connection. She didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t know how long she would be here, or what the future held, but for now, she was grateful for this moment. For the chance to see her mother as she truly was\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 not as the stern, distant figure Haruki knew, but as the kind, vibrant girl walking beside her.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 As they approached the edge of the forest, Honoka pointed down a narrow path. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93My house is just down that way,\u8221\'94 she said. \u8220\'93Where\u8217\'92s your cabin, Haruki-chan?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki glanced toward the dense trees, her heart pounding. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s\u8230\'85 a little further in,\u8221\'94 she said, her voice quiet. \u8220\'93I\u8217\'92ll be fine from here. Thanks for walking with me, Honoka-san.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Honoka smiled, her eyes crinkling at the corners. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Of course! See you tomorrow, Haruki-chan.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Haruki watched as Honoka walked away, her figure growing smaller as she disappeared down the path. For a moment, Haruki stood there, her chest tight with emotion. Then, she turned and made her way into the forest, her footsteps slow and deliberate.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 The small, abandoned house came into view, its silhouette stark against the fading light. Haruki stepped inside, the air cool and still. She sat down on the floor, her back against the wall, and closed her eyes.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 She didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t know how she had ended up here, or why, but one thing was clear: she had been given a chance to see her parents as they truly were\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 not as the stern, distant figures she knew, but as the people they had been before life had shaped them.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 And maybe, just maybe, she could change things. For them. For herself.}
